Setting up a MySQL server on Ubuntu 12.04 LTS

1) Install mysql
   sudo apt-get install mysql-server
   <when prompted, set a root password>

2) Let mysql listen remotely
   sudo vim /etc/mysql/my.conf, and change:
   bind-address = 0.0.0.0 (all interfaces) instead of 127.0.0.1 (only loopback)

3) Add the myria user and the test database
   mysql -u root -p mysql
   <type in the root password>

   CREATE -- USER 'myria'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY '<password>'; -- remove all the --
   CREATE database myria_test;
   GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON myria_test.* TO 'myria'@'%' WITH GRANT OPTION;
   FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

4) run the reset_db.sh script to set up the initial table state.
